^B@2^*BMM: ^*NThis short tutorial briefly explains Crawling Stayman. You can use Standard Stayman only when you have at least one four card major and more than 7 points. However, responder to a 1N opener may have hands with 7 or less points with certain required distribution. Experts endlessly modify those requirements and name them Garbage Stayman, Crawling Stayman, Junk Stayman, to name a few. Here we look at the Crawling Stayman. Let us look at a few examples. In all the responder's hand is weak @- 7 points or less and 4-4 in majors.

For a comprehensive tutorial on responding to 1N opening please refer to |CP|1|fp|2|AT|^*Hhttp://www.bridgesights.com/hondobridge/hondoviewer/hondoviewer.php?sf-ntauctions, Constructive Auctions after a 1NT Opening Bid^*N|CP||fp||at| at Howard Schutzman's website.|
